If you want people to adopt your tool, you may need to explain any advantage this has over fastmcp.<p>It&#x27;s already easy to expose a python function as an MCP server. From the fastmcp docs:<p><pre><code>  from fastmcp import FastMCP

  mcp = FastMCP(&quot;Demo &quot;)

  @mcp.tool
  def add(a: int, b: int) -&gt; int:
      &quot;&quot;&quot;Add two numbers&quot;&quot;&quot;
      return a + b

  if __name__ == &quot;__main__&quot;:
      mcp.run()</code></pre>
